The breakfast buffet was excellent, we didnt need to eat for the rest of the day, the fresh stawberries and raspberries were a real treat.	Had dinner once at the Bridges restaurant, the service was good and so was the food.	The food at the restaurant was good, not amazing, and the service a bit slow although restaurant was only half full.	I love the room service kitchen, breakfast, lunch, and dinner were all truly wonderful and their coffee was so good.	We had room service, the food was decent quality, but the menu is limited, great croque monsieur though.